            <biogHist>
                <p>John MacDonald, farmer, was the son of Roderick MacDonald, merchant, and Marjory
                    MacDonald neé MacLeod. He was married to Mary MacDonald neé MacLellan and they
                    had at least 6 children: Marjory, Donald, Ronald, Roderica, Catherine and
                    Donalda. He died of general decay in July 1864 and his nephew Roderick MacDonald
                    was the informant. </p>
                <p>John is noted in Carmichael's notebooks as having found a bronze brooch and
                    pin.</p>
